// Temporary raw SurrealQL escape hatch.
//
// This top-level form exists so we can test parsing, JSON AST extraction, and
// raw emission before Aurora has first-class syntax for the features that need
// embedded SurrealQL.
//
// Revisit this when these features land:
// - events: action bodies
// - functions: function bodies
// - access: signup/signin expressions
// - field/table permissions: WHERE-style expressions
// - field assertions: boolean expressions
// - computed tables/views: SELECT bodies
//
// The final design should allow `#surql` only in those specific contexts, not
// anywhere in the schema.
#surql {
  DEFINE EVENT audit_user ON TABLE user WHEN $event = "CREATE" THEN {
    CREATE audit SET user = $after.id, action = $event;
  };
}
